	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64190198"><p>Partially agree, but overhead wires are a PAIN to implement and maintain.  The solution to this is to install induction chargers below the street at bus stops.  While stopping for a few minutes, charge the (smaller) battery.  No fuss with plugging in, overhead wires, etc., and the constant small charges are better for the battery anyways.

</p><p>There are fixes for EV issues, but the right needs to stop bitchin' about them, the left needs to stop glossing over them (and forcing people into them by threatening ICE bans), and we ALL need to work to improve EVs.  ICE vehicles were terrible when they first came out (seriously, starting one could kill you), but we didn't throw them away and stick to horses.</p></div>
